windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 610 to 642?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
C) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.C: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

windows.answer: B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.

windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 840 to 858?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
C) Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
options.C: Sudden Increase anomaly: Values show an unexpected surge relative to adjacent points.

windows.answer: A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
